
# Code Review Findings (aufnahmetests branch)

## Blocking / Correctness

- [x] **Autosave watch resubscribes on every onSave identity change** — pinned `onSave` via `onSaveRef` in both AufnahmeForm and HorizonForm; watch effect now has empty deps. First-tick guard now holds across re-renders.

- [x] **Inconsistent controlled/uncontrolled inputs in HorizonForm** — all five uncontrolled inputs (horizontname, tiefe_oben, tiefe_unten, ph_cacl2, notizen) converted to `Controller`. Now any `setValue` call re-renders the input visually.

- [x] **`tonanteil` is local state in HorizonForm, not persisted** — persisted as a new `tonanteil` TEXT column on horizonte. Migration added in db.ts, threaded through Horizont type, saveHorizont, HorizontFormData, form defaults, the Tonanteil input (now Controller-driven), the humus_pct auto-calc dependency, [nr].tsx save call, and CSV export.

- [x] **`farbe_rgb` is dead schema** — dropped. Removed from `Horizont` type, `saveHorizont` SQL/params, `[nr].tsx`'s hardcoded null, db.ts CREATE TABLE schema, and CSV export type + buildRows. Old DBs keep the orphan column (SQLite CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS); new installs don't have it.

- [x] **CSV export missing `effektiver_wurzelraum`** — added to AufnahmeCSVRow and buildRows.

## Important

- [x] **`Rating` type vs implementation mismatch** — documented as intentional (KA6 thresholds differ per metric). Added JSDoc above the type explaining the superset shape.

- [x] **Autosave fires on every keystroke** — added `useDebouncedCallback` hook (utils/useDebouncedCallback.ts) at 250 ms, wired into both standort.tsx and [nr].tsx. Pending writes flush on unmount so navigating away doesn't drop the last edit.

- [x] **`A`-horizon detection is over-loose** — tightened to `/^[a-z]*A/` so it matches Ah/Ap/fAh/rAp but not BvA or names where A appears mid-string.

- [x] **Unused `useRef` import** — removed from `[nr].tsx`. (Forms' imports verified — all used.)

- [x] **`createAufnahme` race on nummer** — collapsed to one `INSERT … SELECT COALESCE(MAX(nummer),0)+1 …` statement. Same fix applied to `addHorizont`.

## Maintainability / Nice-to-have

- [x] **AufnahmeForm.tsx is 1500+ lines** — moved EXPOS / RELIEFPOS_OPTIONS / WITTERUNG_OPTIONS / NUTZUNG_SECTIONS / VEGETATION_SECTIONS into `utils/aufnahmeOptions.ts`. AufnahmeForm shrank by ~290 lines.

- [x] **Repeated TextInput blocks in AufnahmeForm extended section** — collapsed 17 near-identical `<Controller><TextInput/></Controller>` blocks into a `.map()` over `[name, label, placeholder]` tuples.

- [x] **Keyboard avoidance logic duplicated** — extracted `useNotizenScroll` hook (utils/useNotizenScroll.ts). Both standort.tsx and HorizonForm now use it; duplicated Animated/Keyboard plumbing gone from both.

- [~] **CSV row types duplicate DB types** — left as-is. Refactor was non-trivial and the immediate drift (effektiver_wurzelraum, tonanteil) has been fixed. Worth revisiting if a third field drifts.

- [x] **`useEffect` exhaustive-deps lint** — added `setValue` to the dep arrays of every effect that uses it in HorizonForm and AufnahmeForm. (RHF's setValue is stable so behaviour is unchanged.)

- [x] **tools/index.tsx has 11 near-identical Link blocks** — replaced with a `TOOL_SECTIONS` array and one `.map()`. ~110 LOC → ~90 LOC, and easier to reorder/add tools.

- [x] **Orphan docstring in app/mapping/index.tsx** — fixed: gave `handleExport` its own short docstring and moved the "create new Feldkampagne" docstring above `handleCreate`.

- [x] **`BasensaettigungLookup.CURVE_4TO15` has data gap** — annotated as intentional with a comment explaining the linear-interp behaviour across BS 65/70 %.

- [x] **Status-derivation logic should live closer to schema** — exported `HORIZONT_REQUIRED_FOR_VOLLSTAENDIG` from HorizonQueries.ts and `STANDORT_REQUIRED_FOR_VOLLSTAENDIG` from MappingQueries.ts. `saveHorizont.isFull` and `deriveStandortStatus` now iterate those arrays. Adding a new required field is now a one-line change.

- [x] **JSON.parse without try/catch in csvExport** — gone with `farbe_rgb` removal.

- [x] **Magic horizon-class regex** — kept inline with a clarifying comment (only one call site). If a second consumer appears, extract `isAHorizon()` then.

---

# Code Review Findings (older components & utils)

## Blocking / Correctness

- [x] **`initDatabase()` runs on every render of RootLayout** — wrapped in `useEffect(() => initDatabase(), [])`. Schema + migrations now run once on mount.

- [x] **`farbe_rgb` is dead schema (also flagged in branch review)** — see branch review entry above; dropped throughout.

- [x] **PictureTaker doesn't dispose Skia image** — added `image.dispose()` in a `finally` block.

- [x] **`anmoorig_*` entries in PoreLookUp are unreachable** — kept as reference data with a `// TODO: currently unreachable …` comment so future contributors know they need a horizonname-based dispatch to use them.

- [x] **Stale grid-axis comment in renger1987** — comment now reflects the actual 4 × 3 × 4 grid. Removed the misleading "All values are NaN — replace with numbers from your diagram" note (values are populated).

## Important

- [x] **`munsellLookup.rgbToMunsell` does 2N Lab conversions per call** — entry Labs precomputed once at module load into `MUNSELL_LAB`; input Lab converted once per call. Also switched to squared-distance comparison so the per-entry `sqrt` is gone (one sqrt at the end for the returned distance).

- [x] **`DropdownField` modal closes on inner taps** — gone with DropdownField (see next entry).

- [x] **DropdownField and LabeledDropdownField are 90% identical** — deleted DropdownField. LabeledDropdownField now accepts `string[]` as a shorthand for code-only options and renders the label conditionally. Two call sites in AufnahmeForm migrated.

- [x] **HorizonButton and StatusBadge use two different badge implementations** — extracted shared `<Badge label color>` component (components/Badge.tsx). HorizonButton, StatusBadge, and the Standortdaten row in `[aufnahmeId]/index.tsx` all use it now.

- [x] **`HorizontLexikonContent` and `HumusformLexikonContent` duplicate ~95% of structure** — extracted generic `<LexikonContent>` (search bar, SectionList, filter useMemo, scroll-to-top-on-filter, sticky headers). Both wrappers now only supply data, filter predicate, renderItem, and styling.

- [x] **`DecisionTree` history setter is non-functional** — switched both `handlePress` and `handleBack` to functional updaters (`setHistory(h => …)`). Rapid taps no longer drop entries.

- [x] **`DecisionTree` silent dead-end on missing node** — `getNode` now `console.warn`s the missing id (with the tree id for context) before returning the stub. Easier to diagnose malformed trees in dev.

- [x] **`createAufnahme` race on `MAX(nummer) + 1`** — fixed above (also `addHorizont`).

## Maintainability / Nice-to-have

- [x] **PictureTaker overlay rectangles vs extractor rectangles are loosely coupled** — centralized in `utils/cameraOverlay.ts` with both a `display` and a `sample` rect per region. PictureTaker reads display fractions; soilColorExtractor reads sample fractions via `getSamplingRect()`. Height mismatch between display and sample is now explicit + documented.

- [x] **`SoilShareScroll` over-commented** — pared down to ~5 WHY-comments. Removed the stale "Squares are 80 % of cell size" line and dozens of what-comments. File is ~30 lines shorter.

- [x] **`PictureTaker.tsx` typo** — "Fotofchhandel" → "Fotofachhandel".

- [x] **`about.tsx` typos** — "Excelübetragung" → "Excelübertragung"; "Diese Problem" → "Dieses Problem".

- [~] **`Dimensions.get('window')` captured at module load** — deferred. Soil-mapping app currently runs portrait-locked, so rotation isn't an active concern.

- [x] **`chromaToClass` inlined in HumusgehaltTool and HorizonForm** — both now call the exported `chromaToClass(chroma)` from renger1987.

- [~] **`bodenart → clay %` vs `KAK_BASE`** — deferred. Tables are domain-correct as-is; consolidate only if a third bodenart-keyed table appears.

- [x] **`Skia.Image.readPixels()` byte order assumption** — documented in soilColorExtractor.ts. If a future Skia returns BGRA the comment points to the swap.

- [x] **`utmConversion` has no domain validation** — documented the supported range and the unhandled special-zone exceptions in the `latLonToUTM` JSDoc. For German use cases (typical inputs) this is sufficient; clamping would silently mask out-of-range input.

- [x] **`parseDensityMidpoint` invents midpoints for ">1.65" and "<1.45"** — kept the name (callers untouched) but expanded the JSDoc to clearly call out that bounded forms return a heuristic ±0.15 representative, not a true midpoint, and that the offset is paired with the density-class boundaries.

- [x] **`humusGroup` in BasensaettigungTool is private** — exported `humusGroupLabel(humusPctStr)` from BasensaettigungLookup; BasensaettigungTool calls it instead of its own local copy.

- [x] **`ResetInstructionButton` style overrides clash with `styles.resetButton`** — dropped the absolute positioning from the default `resetButton` style (now visual-only). Callers in PictureTaker, DecisionTree, mapping/index, and SoilShareScroll now pass minimal positioning that no longer fights the base style.

- [x] **Duplicate `formatDate` helper** — moved to `utils/formatDate.ts`; both screens import it.

- [x] **`kampagne/[kampagneId]/index.tsx` empty StyleSheet** — deleted (and dropped the now-unused `StyleSheet` import).

- [x] **N+1 horizon count in campaign detail screen** — added `getAufnahmenWithHorizontCount(sessionId)` that returns aufnahmen + COUNT(horizonte) in one SQL query via correlated subquery. The screen calls it instead of the per-row `getHorizonteForAufnahme().length`.

- [x] **`FlatList renderItem` destructures unused `index`** — removed.

- [~] **`InstructionModal` remount-via-key pattern** — deferred. Pattern is consistent across all callers and works fine.

- [~] **`Link href={"/mapping" as any}`** — deferred. Awaiting expo-router typegen; will resolve itself on upgrade.

